Hepatic trauma: CT findings and considerations based on our experience in emergency diagnostic imaging. Abdominal blunt trauma represents the main cause of death in people of age less than 40 years the liver injury occurs frequently, with an incidence varying from 3 to 10%. Isolated hepatic lesions are rare and in 77-90% of cases, lesions of other organs and viscera are involved. Right hepatic lobe is a frequent site of injury, because it is the more voluminous portion of liver parenchyma